7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Podcastle and Soundraw share a solid foundation of core features including . Where Podcastle pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Text To Speech and Voice Cloning and Speech To Text and Noise Removal and Podcast Editing and Custom Voices, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, Soundraw uniquely offers Music Generation, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Podcastle holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 8/10, while Soundraw scores 6/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Podcastle offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $11.99/mo, compared to Soundraw's starting price of $16.99/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Podcastle's free tier and Soundraw's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
